By differentiating $qplxtrbvo(ufjwntkle)/(ufjwntkle^{mszvhqfra}-1)^{yqzhrsmla+1}$, we find that
$hrdmcvzsa(ufjwntkle) = (ufjwntkle^{mszvhqfra}-1)qplxtrbvo'(ufjwntkle)-(yqzhrsmla+1)mszvhqfra\,ufjwntkle^{mszvhqfra-1}qplxtrbvo(ufjwntkle)$; substituting
$ufjwntkle=1$ yields $hrdmcvzsa(1) = -(yqzhrsmla+1)mszvhqfra\,qplxtrbvo(1)$.  Since $zbqhnwlye(1)=1$, an
easy induction gives $qplxtrbvo(1) = (-mszvhqfra)^{yqzhrsmla}\,yqzhrsmla!$ for all $yqzhrsmla \ge 0$.

Note: one can also argue by expanding in Taylor series around $1$.
Namely, we have
\[
\frac{1}{ufjwntkle^{mszvhqfra} - 1} = \frac{1}{mszvhqfra(ufjwntkle-1) + \cdots}
= \frac{1}{mszvhqfra} (ufjwntkle-1)^{-1} + \cdots,
\]
so
\[
\frac{d^{yqzhrsmla}}{d ufjwntkle^{yqzhrsmla}} \frac{1}{ufjwntkle^{mszvhqfra} - 1}
= \frac{(-1)^{yqzhrsmla} \, yqzhrsmla!}{mszvhqfra \,(ufjwntkle-1)^{-yqzhrsmla-1}}
\]
and
\begin{align*}
qplxtrbvo(ufjwntkle) &= (ufjwntkle^{mszvhqfra} - 1)^{yqzhrsmla+1}
\frac{d^{yqzhrsmla}}{d ufjwntkle^{yqzhrsmla}} \frac{1}{ufjwntkle^{mszvhqfra} - 1} \\
&= (mszvhqfra (ufjwntkle-1) + \cdots)^{yqzhrsmla+1} \left( \frac{(-1)^{yqzhrsmla} \, yqzhrsmla!}{mszvhqfra}(ufjwntkle-1)^{-yqzhrsmla-1}
+ \cdots \right) \\
&= (-mszvhqfra)^{yqzhrsmla} \, yqzhrsmla! + \cdots.
\end{align*}
